Global Rubella Diagnostic Testing Market Insights
Rubella Diagnostic Testing Market size was valued at USD 0.25 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 0.45 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.9% from 2024 to 2030.

Rubella Diagnostic Testing Market Overview
The global Rubella diagnostic testing market is valued at approximately USD 3.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to expand at a CAGR of 5.2% over the forecast period. This growth is driven by increased awareness about the importance of vaccination and early detection of rubella infections. With the rise in global healthcare infrastructure, especially in emerging economies, diagnostic tests for rubella have gained significant traction. Additionally, the growing efforts to eradicate rubella and congenital rubella syndrome (CRS) contribute to the market's growth. Government initiatives, such as vaccination campaigns, are also key drivers of market expansion.

